The truck collided with four vehicles at the intersection of East and Stapleton roads. JOHANNESBURG - A 50-year-old truck driver has died in a freak accident in Pinetown. The truck collided with four vehicles at the intersection of East and Stapleton roads. READ: Four people survive after collision on N12 It went down the embankment and into a residential property, causing severe damage. Paramedics tried, unsuccessfully, to resuscitate the driver. No other injuries were reported.